data.title: Benigno Aquino Iii
data.meta_description: Corazon Aquino - Free download as Word Doc (.doc), PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. Corazon Aquino was the first female president of the Philippines. She led the 1986 People Power Revolution that overthrew Ferdinand Marcos, restoring democracy. Her husband Benigno Aquino Jr. had been assassinated in 1983 after criticizing Marcos, making her a leader of the opposition. In the 1986 election declared fraudulent, Aquino called for protests and was installed as president on February 25, 1986. She established a new constitution limiting presidential powers and focused on civil liberties, peace talks, and economic recovery.
